    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, p. 111, n. <citedRange>85</citedRange>, fig. 41</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.197</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>024100</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, p. <citedRange>204</citedRange> (date of the base)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>202</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.50</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63443"><name nymRef="#Δαϊμένης">Δαϊμένης</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65790"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Τηλόξηνος">Τηλοξήνω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Daimenes fils de Teloxenos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Daimenes son of Teloxenos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Daimenes figlio di Teloxenos.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The round hollow on top, normally, is not a good clue for a funerary use; neither is the shape of the stone without mouldings, although Beschi mentions it 
                    amongst his first group of funerary bases. However, Oliverio mentioned as provenance the 'South-Eastern Necropolis' (which is in fact the Eastern one).
                    The question should remain open.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
